In this example, the kernel is a Gaussian kernel, which is a smoothing kernel that gives higher weights to pixels closer to the center and lower weights to pixels farther away. This produces a blur effect that is more pronounced in the center and less pronounced at the edges.

To use this shader, you would bind the image you want to blur to the `image` uniform and set the `resolution` uniform to the resolution of the image. Then, you can draw a quad with the shader applied to blur the image.

